isHolder(address).details: This function checks if the wallet has a balance greater than zero

returns._0: bool indicating whether the wallet is a holder

mint(uint256).details: Reverts if the token is already minted, if the address is zero, or if the max supply is reached

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to mint

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

ownerOfToken(uint256).details: This function overrides the ownerOf function from ERC721Enumerable

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to get the owner for

returns._0: The address of the owner of the token

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setBaseURI(string).details: Only callable by the owner of the contract

params._newBaseURI: The new base URI to set

params.tokenId: The ID of the token to get the URI for

returns._0: The token URI as a string

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

mint(uint256).notice: Mint a token to a the sender address

ownerOfToken(uint256).notice: Get the owner of a specific token ID
